ptions         Home / Undergraduate Catalog / Colleges & Departments / College of Liberal Arts and Sciences / Polish, Russian, and Lithuanian Studies / Minor in Central and Eastern European Studies   Minor in Central and Eastern European Studies       Students from other disciplines who want to minor in Central and Eastern European Studies must complete 12 semester hours, including:   Course List         Code  Title  Hours     Required Courses  CEES 224 Introduction to Literary Analysis of Central Eastern European Texts 3  or CEES 225 Introduction to Central and Eastern European Cultures  Nine hours of course work in Central and Eastern European Studies at the 100, 200, 300, or 400 level. A minimum of 6 semester hours must be at the 200 level or above. 9  Total Hours 12   Note: Polish courses, Russian courses, Lithuanian courses, and history courses with a focus on Polish and Russian Studies and Jewish Studies may be used to satisfy the 9-semester-hour requirement, as approved by the director of undergraduate studies. No more than 3 hours in courses cross listed with the Department of History may be applied to the minor.          University of Illinois at Chicago   Apply Online | Contact Admissions | Privacy Statement Having problems accessing this site? Contact the Webmaster . © 2018-2019 The Board of Trustees of the University of Illinois    Back to Top   Print Options     Send Page to Printer    Print this page.    Download PDF of this page The PDF will include all information unique to this page.    Download PDF of the entire Undergraduate Catalog    All pages in the campus catalog.       Cancel    